games.comment: DeAndre Hopkins led to an overtime win. The Titans came close to being 2-0 with road wins at Houston and Pittsburgh, but the Tennessee secondary couldn't close out the win for the team to now be 1-1. The Titans were down 14-10 at the start of the 4.h quarter when

DeAndre Hopkins, who made some ridiculous catches in this contest. He started right away with a 1.handed grab on the opening drive. He then made a terrific toe-tap reception for 17 yards along the sideline. Hopkins tortured Tennessee's secondary, but didn't finish with a great stat line; he had 8 catches for 80 yards. He nearly scored a touchdown in the opening quarter, but managed to get just 1 foot inbounds. As for Savage's other weapons, tight end Stephen Anderson was next on the stat sheet with 5 catches for 79 yards and a touchdown.
